"title": "8476: self-discipline",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8476",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The dedicated training, through the study of Scripture, prayer and self-control, which enables Christians to be more effective witnesses to the gospel, to lead lives more pleasing to God, and to win the crown that awaits those who are victorious over sin.</p>\n<h2>Self-discipline is training oneself to be godly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:7\">1TI 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:14\">ROM 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:24-1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:24–9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:23-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:23–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:12-Phil3:14\">PHP 3:12–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:7\">2TI 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:14\">HEB 5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1\">HEB 12:1</a></p>\n<h2>Self-discipline and the study of Scripture</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:9-Ps119:11\">PSA 119:9–119:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:16-2Tim3:17\">2TI 3:16–3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:29\">DEU 29:29</a></p>\n<h2>Self-discipline involves learning through experience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12\">TIT 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:3-Rom5:5\">ROM 5:3–5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Self-discipline should transform the whole person</h2>\n<h3>A Christian's thoughts should be disciplined</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:5\">2CO 10:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:3\">ROM 12:3</a>ROM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:23\">EPH 4:23</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:7\">1PE 4:7</a></p>\n<h3>A Christian's speech should be disciplined</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:3\">PSA 141:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:2-Jas3:12\">JAS 3:2–3:12</a></p>\n<h3>A Christian's behaviour should be disciplined</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:20-Rom14:21\">ROM 14:20–14:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A Christian's body should be disciplined</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12-Rom6:13\">ROM 6:12–6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22\">EPH 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:2\">JAS 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>Self-discipline prevents God's discipline</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:31-1Cor11:32\">1CO 11:31–11:32</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Physical self-discipline is of some value, but only in this life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:8\">1TI 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:25\">1CO 9:25</a></p>\n<h2>An elder should be self-disciplined</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:8\">TIT 1:8</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of those who exercised self-discipline</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:9-Gen22:14\">GEN 22:9–22:14</a> <em>Abraham</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:8-Gen39:12\">GEN 39:8–39:12</a> <em>Joseph</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:11-2Sam11:13\">2SA 11:11–11:13</a> <em>Uriah</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:8\">DAN 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:11-Dan1:13\">DAN 1:11–1:13</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a> <em>Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:13</a> <em>Paul</em></p>\n<h2>Self-discipline strengthens believers when faced with temptation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:29\">MAT 5:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:47\">MRK 9:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13\">ROM 8:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a></p>\n<h2>The reward for self-discipline is a crown and a prize</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:25\">1CO 9:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:24\">1CO 9:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:14\">PHP 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:18\">COL 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:19\">1TH 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:12\">JAS 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:11\">REV 3:11</a></p>",
